drop api_paste_ini support

This is not used in OpenStack modules anymore.

Implement the MODULE::db and MODULE::params class

This review aims to update the puppet-openstack compliant module
skeleton to add :

 * MODULE::db: This class allow to configure the database connection
for the service. It offers the same parameters (ie. level of
customization) across all our modules

 * MODULE::params: This class allow to specify class' specific param.
They can be conditioned by the osfamily type

Update keystone::auth service name parameter

To be consistent and allow for username changes for services that may
not have the service name itself in, we need to provide the default
service name as a parameter when configuring the keystone information.
This change updates the cookiecutter keystone auth class to set the
service_name to the project name by default.

Add retries to db-sync

If db-sync fails, it will not be rerun until a configuration change or a
package update. This can lead to misconfigured databases, so we should
at least attempt to retry the sync process.

Add hooks for external install & svc management

This adds defined anchor points for external modules to hook into the
software install, config and service dependency chain.  This allows
external modules to manage software installation (virtualenv,
containers, etc) and service management (pacemaker) without needing rely
on resources that may change or be renamed.

Configure *_domain_name to Default by default

Keystone v2.0 API was removed so we have no choice but configuring
user_domain_name and project_domain_name otherwise it fallbacks to
Keystone v2.0 and it fails. This patch sets the default value so we make
sure Keystone v3 will be used out of the box for our users.
